{{Infobox video game | image = | caption = | developer = 2.0 Studios | publisher = 2.0 Studios | designer = Daniel Armstrong and Jarryd Semmens | artist= | composer = | engine = | released = December 13, 2011 | genre = [[Sandbox game|Sandbox]] | modes = [[Single-player]] | platforms = [[Windows Phone]] }}
'''''CraftWorld''''' is a video game released as an alpha on [[Windows Phone Store]] on December 13, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wp7lab.com/news/craft-world-indie-game-launches-windows-phone/ |title=Craft World Indie Game Launches on Windows Phone |accessdate=May 4, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120402143413/http://wp7lab.com/news/craft-world-indie-game-launches-windows-phone/ |archivedate=April 2, 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://winsource.com/2011/12/14/minecraft-clone-craftworld-now-available-on-wp7/|title=Minecraft-clone Craftworld Now Available on WP7|work=Winsource.com|accessdate=2015-07-24}}</ref> ''CraftWorld'' cites ''[[Minecraft]]'', ''[[Infiniminer]]'' and ''[[The Elder Scrolls IV: Oblivion]]'' as direct inspirations for the game. The game utilizes textured [[voxel]]s to simulate blended biomes based on temperature.
The game currently has two versions, paid and free, with a third mode (beta) to be added. Both the free and paid versions have been updated to version 2.5, which includes many new features, such as enemy characters that will attack the player. Crafting, building and collecting have all been added in the recent versions.
==Ports== It has been announced that ''CraftWorld'' was to be released on the [[Xbox Live]] [[Xbox Live Marketplace|Marketplace]] and on the Seb P's iPad in June 2012.{{citation needed|date=August 2012}} The Xbox 360 version of ''CraftWorld'', called ''Block World'' on the platform, was released on [[Xbox Live Indie Games]] on August 17, 2012.
