{{Infobox comic book title <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics--> |title = Garin's uncanny file |image = Garin-malaycover01.jpg |imagesize = 180 |caption = The first comic volumes of Garin's uncanny file published in Malaysia. |schedule = |format = comic, novel |limited = Y |ongoing = Y |1shot = |genre = |Adventure = |Fantasy = Y |publisher = [[Punica Publishing|Punica]] (Thailand) |date = |startmo = July |startyr = 2008 |endmo = |endyr = |issues = |main_char_team = Garin, Lultima |writers = [[Aii (writer)|Aii]] |artists = [[Black Tohfu]] |pencillers = |inkers = |letterers = |colorists = |editors = |creative_team_month = |creative_team_year = |creators = |TPB = |ISBN = |TPB# = |ISBN# = |subcat = Thai comics |altcat = |sort = Garin&#39;s uncanny file |addpubcat# = |nonUS = }} '''Garin's uncanny file''' ({{lang-th|การิน ปริศนาคดีอาถรรพ์}}) is a Thai comic series written by [[Aii (writer)|Aii]] and illustrated by [[Black Tohfu (manga writer)|Black Tohfu ]] . It was originally serialized in [[Thailand]] by [[Punica Publishing]].<ref>2010. '''A BRIEF HISTORY OF THAI COMICS AND GRAPHIC NOVELS'''. LET'S Comic Publishing. {{ISBN|978-616-90128-6-3}}, p. 314.</ref>
Garin's uncanny file phenomenon created within one month of sales released and published in [[Malaysia]] as ''FaIL aNEH GaRIN''<ref>[http://punica.co.th/garin/2009/02/13/“fail-aneh-garin”-หนังสือการ์ตูนลิขส Garin's uncanny file in Malaysia]</ref>
Garin’s Uncanny File has three versions: novel, comic, and BlaCX. There is also a live-action film adaption called Garin X Guardian released in theaters in 2015.
==Summary== Lultima is a girl with an extraordinary ability. Because of it evil things keep coming to her. She also can read people's minds. She tries to escape from them all the time. After transferring to a new school she met a boy named Garin, who's fond of black magic. Then there was an accident with a student in her class, which Lultima sensed it might be because of Garin.
==Characters== {{Main|List of characters in Garin's uncanny file}}
==Reception== Garin's Uncanny File is the best selling book of both [[Thailand]] and [[Malaysia]]. And now has plan to sign a contract to purchase in many countries. Also [[South Korea]] that be next country.<ref>Matichon Newspaper February 12, 2011 vol.12026 page 24</ref>
