{{Infobox building | name = Iwami Art Museum | native_name = 島根県立石見美術館 | image = Grand Toit.jpg | caption = Grand Toit | cost = | owner = | address = 5-15 Ariake-chō | location_town = [[Masuda, Shimane|Masuda]], [[Shimane Prefecture]] | location_country = [[Japan]] | coordinates = {{coord|34.67298358|N|131.84808424|E|display=title,inline|format=dms|type:landmark_region:JP_scale:10000}} | opened_date = 8 October 2005 | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = | demolition_date = | destruction_date = | other_dimensions = | floor_count = | floor_area = | architect = | architecture_firm = | url = {{homepage|http://www.grandtoit.jp/english/index.html}} }}
{{nihongo|'''Iwami Art Museum'''|島根県立石見美術館|Shimane Kenritsu Iwami Bijutsukan}} opened in [[Masuda, Shimane|Masuda]], [[Shimane Prefecture]], Japan, in 2005. Together with {{nihongo|Iwami Arts Theatre|島根県立いわみ芸術劇場}} it forms part of the {{nihongo|Shimane Arts Centre|[[:ja:島根県芸術文化センター グラントワ|島根県芸術文化センター]]}}, also known as {{nihongo|Grand Toit|グラントワ}}, the French for "large roof". The collection includes works by {{nihongo|Kanō Shōei|[[:ja:狩野松栄|狩野松栄]]}}, [[Unkoku Togan|Unkoku Tōgan]], [[Kuroda Seiki]], [[Fujishima Takeji]], [[Okada Saburōsuke]], and [[Kishida Ryūsei]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pref.shimane.lg.jp/admin/seisaku/koho/esque/2007/No63/p11-12.html |script-title=ja:島根県立石見美術館 |trans-title=Iwami Art Museum |language=Japanese |publisher=[[Shimane Prefecture]] |accessdate=27 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.grandtoit.jp/about/concept/index.html#history |script-title=ja:グラントワについて |trans-title=About Grand Toit |language=Japanese |publisher=Grand Toit |accessdate=27 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.grandtoit.jp/museum/artworks/list.html |script-title=ja:収蔵品一覧 |trans-title=List of the Collection |language=Japanese |publisher=Grand Toit |accessdate=27 February 2016}}</ref>
